---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title={"See Your Open Tabs on Every Device with Encrypted Tab Sync | Blanc"}
  description={"Blanc's Tab Sync shows your open tabs from your other devices — end-to-end encrypted, off by default, opt-in per device, and never a merged live session."}
  path="/features/sync"
  page="feature-sync"
  current="features"
  ogDescription={"Your open tabs from your other devices — end-to-end encrypted, off by default, opt-in per device."}
  ogImageAlt={"Blanc Browser"}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline slot="head">
{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://blancbrowser.com/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Features","item":"https://blancbrowser.com/features"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Tab sync","item":"https://blancbrowser.com/features/sync"}]}
</script>

<main class="feature-page feature-detail-page">
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">home</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><a href="/features">features</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><span aria-current="page">tab sync</span></nav>
  <section class="feature-hero feature-hero--detail feature-hero--text" aria-labelledby="sync-title"><p class="section-kicker">pick up anywhere</p><h1 id="sync-title">Your open tabs, on your other devices.</h1><p>Turn on sharing and each machine publishes what it has open. Browse another device&rsquo;s tabs from the Island, the Quick Switcher, or the start page — and open one locally with a click.</p></section>
  <figure class="product-capture feature-capture">
    <div class="demo-stage island-figure island-figure--panel" role="img" aria-label="Blanc's Island panel open, showing local tabs and a folded section from another device: blanc on MacBook Air with three tabs.">
      <div class="demo-page" aria-hidden="true"><div class="bar w1"></div><div class="bar w2"></div><div class="bar w3"></div><div class="bar w4"></div></div>
      <picture>
        <source media="(max-width: 560px)" srcset="/shots/mobile/netflix.jpg">
        <img class="demo-shot show" src="/shots/desktop/netflix.jpg" loading="lazy" alt="" aria-hidden="true">
      </picture>
      <div class="demo-island open" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="panel">
          <div class="panel-row"><div class="field"><span class="typed"></span><span class="caret"></span></div></div>
          <div class="list">
            <div class="trow"><span class="fav" style="background-image:url('https://icons.duckduckgo.com/ip3/gmail.com.ico')"></span><span class="title">Gmail</span><span class="dom">mail.google.com</span></div>
            <div class="trow"><span class="fav" style="background-image:url('https://icons.duckduckgo.com/ip3/notion.so.ico')"></span><span class="title">Notion</span><span class="dom">notion.so</span></div>
            <div class="sec-head"><svg class="caret" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3.5 2 L7 5 L3.5 8"/></svg><span>blanc on MacBook Air</span><span class="rule"></span><span class="count">2h ago</span></div>
            <div class="trow"><span class="fav" style="background-image:url('https://icons.duckduckgo.com/ip3/github.com.ico')"></span><span class="title">Pull requests</span><span class="dom">github.com</span></div>
            <div class="trow hl"><span class="fav" style="background-image:url('https://icons.duckduckgo.com/ip3/developer.mozilla.org.ico')"></span><span class="title">MDN Web Docs</span><span class="dom">developer.mozilla.org</span></div>
            <div class="trow"><span class="fav" style="background-image:url('https://icons.duckduckgo.com/ip3/news.ycombinator.com.ico')"></span><span class="title">Hacker News</span><span class="dom">news.ycombinator.com</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="foot">esc to dismiss · ⌘L summons · click a row to open it here</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <figcaption>Another device&rsquo;s tabs appear as a quiet folded section. Opening one never changes anything on the other machine.</figcaption>
  </figure>
  <section class="feature-copy-grid feature-copy-grid--top" aria-labelledby="sync-behavior-title">
    <div><p class="section-kicker">a menu, not a mirror</p><h2 id="sync-behavior-title">Reading another device never rearranges it.</h2></div>
    <div class="feature-copy-list">
      <article><h3>Off until you say so, on each device.</h3><p>Sharing is a per-device switch in Settings, off by default. A machine&rsquo;s tabs never leave it until you flip the switch on that machine — and flipping it off withdraws them.</p></article>
      <article><h3>Open here, not there.</h3><p>Another device&rsquo;s tabs are a read-only list. Picking one opens it as a fresh local tab; nothing force-opens, closes, or reorders on the other side.</p></article>
      <article><h3>Everywhere you already look.</h3><p>Remote tabs sit behind a folded section in the Island panel, match in the Quick Switcher below your local tabs, and appear on the start page under &ldquo;on your other devices.&rdquo;</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <aside class="truth-note" aria-labelledby="sync-note-title"><p class="section-kicker">the honest part</p><h2 id="sync-note-title">The sync server stores ciphertext it cannot read.</h2><p>Tab snapshots ride the same end-to-end encryption as the rest of Blanc sync: encrypted on your device with a key derived from your passphrase, stored server-side as unreadable blobs. Private tabs never enter a snapshot, and idle devices age out on their own.</p><a class="text-link" href="/features/security" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="sync" data-cta-position="related-feature">Read the security story <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a></aside>
  <section class="feature-close" aria-labelledby="sync-close-title"><p class="section-kicker">continue where you were</p><h2 id="sync-close-title">The tab you need is on the other machine. Not anymore.</h2><a class="cta" href="/download" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="sync" data-cta-position="feature-close">download blanc</a></section>
</main>
</BaseLayout>
